content:
To normalize the provided profile data, I'll follow the specified guidelines for company names, job titles, skills, locations, and dates. I'll also include a `normalization_notes` field to document any significant changes or ambiguities. Let's proceed with the normalization:

### Input Profile
```json
{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "title": "VP of Eng.",
  "location": "SF, California",
  "key_skills": [
    "Python",
    "Data Sci",
    "Project Mgmt"
  ],
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "Tech Solutions LLC",
      "title": "VP Eng.",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "Feb 2018",
        "end_date": "Present",
        "date_range": "5 years 8 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco"
    },
    {
      "company": "Innovatech",
      "title": "Sr. Developer",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "March 2015",
        "end_date": "January 2018",
        "date_range": "2 years 10 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, CA"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Normalized Profile
```json
{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "title": "Vice President of Engineering",
  "location": "San Francisco, California, United States",
  "key_skills": [
    "Python",
    "Data Science",
    "Project Management"
  ],
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "Tech Solutions LLC",
      "title": "Vice President of Engineering",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "2018-02",
        "end_date": "Present",
        "date_range": "5 years 8 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, California, United States"
    },
    {
      "company": "Innovatech",
      "title": "Senior Developer",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "2015-03",
        "end_date": "2018-01",
        "date_range": "2 years 10 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, California, United States"
    }
  ],
  "normalization_notes": "Expanded abbreviations for job titles and skills; Standardized SF to full city name."
}
```

### Explanation of Changes
- **Title Normalization**: "VP of Eng." and "VP Eng." were expanded to "Vice President of Engineering".
- **Location Normalization**: "SF, California" and "San Francisco, CA" were standardized to "San Francisco, California, United States".
- **Skills Normalization**: "Data Sci" and "Project Mgmt" were expanded to "Data Science" and "Project Management".
- **Date Normalization**: Dates were converted to ISO format (YYYY-MM).

This normalized profile maintains the semantic meaning of the original data while ensuring consistency for analysis and clustering.
